						<summary>

						<p>On the wall of the east inner <hi rend="italic">gōpura,</hi> Śvētāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 10: 981 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a gift of 25 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tiruveṇkāḍu-dēvar by Sadirayaṉ UttamaśIliyār, wife of the chief of Vannāḍu.<note n="192-1">Eviently this Vannāḍuḍaiyār was the same chief as the one who figures as the donor of 25 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañj</hi> for another perpetual lamp for the same god in the other inscription from the same place dealt with above. (See No. 74).</note>The <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> undertook to protect the gift.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 254.</p>						

						</summary>
